Dominic AdriaansePolice are investigating after four cars were torched in the early hours of Tuesday at UCT s lower campus.The university confirmed the cars, parked in Chapel Road behind the Baxter residence, were set alight at about 2am.UCT has condemned the incident, which follows that at CPUT's Bellville campus on Monday, when six cars were torched.CPUT Fees Must Fall activists have distanced themselves from the attacks, and said their cause for free education had been hijacked by a &quot;third force&quot;.